description: France and some other European countries ease restrictions after two months of lockdown.
title: Coronavirus: France eases lockdown after eight weeks
title_page: Coronavirus: France eases lockdown after eight weeks - BBC News
maintext: What it suggests are two things: first that the real test has not yet come. People are obviously hesitant about resuming their old lives. The risk of a second wave will be when - and if - they actually get back to normal.
